Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of an ontology for rehabilitation therapies following brain injury, which involves knowledge elicitation and information extraction. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for ontology development, computational linguistics (cs.CL) for information extraction, machine learning (cs.LG) for building a corpus, information retrieval (cs.IR) for literature-based approaches, and cybernetics (cs.CY) for the study of control and communication in living organisms.
